# Screen Inventory

## 1. Brief
Purpose: collect the minimum context needed to make the rehearsal and debrief relevant.

### 1.1 Project Context
Purpose:
- capture the startup idea and narrative foundation.

Key content:
- user copy and paste into text box for the its project context
- upload PDF for pitch deck
- upload notes 

Expected outcome:
- a structured project brief object that can be used downstream in the Room and Debrief phases.

### 1.2 Hackathon Context
Purpose:
- capture event-specific framing so the pitch and evaluation are grounded in the actual judging environment.

Key content:
- user copy and paste the hackathon guidelines into text box

 ## 2. Room
Purpose: simulate the actual performance environment where the founder presents and responds under pressure.[page:211]

This phase is sequential:
1. Pitch
2. Q&A

### 2.1 Pitch
Purpose:
- record the founder’s opening pitch before live questioning.

Key content / functionality:
- video or audio recording interface
- visible timer
- clear prompt to deliver the opening pitch
- minimal distractions
- strong primary CTA to lock the recording and move forward

Expected outcome:
- a pitch recording artifact
- optional transcript / summary for downstream review

### 2.2 Q&A (Gemini Live Agent)
Purpose:
- simulate a live-room style adversarial questioning session with AI judge personas.

Key content / functionality:
- Zoom-like room layout
- founder video as dominant stage
- judge personas in smaller tiles
- active speaker state
- session timer
- transcript / turn capture
- familiar but cinematic room feel
- minimal clutter

Expected outcome:
- a Q&A transcript or structured turn log
- evidence for narrative gaps, delivery weaknesses, and response quality

---

## 3. Debrief (Opus 4.7 Agnet)
Purpose: turn the pitch and Q&A session into a structured post-mortem and coaching loop.

### 3.1 Review
Purpose:
- present the main post-session artifact.

Key content: (SUBJECT FOR REFINEMENT & BRAINSTORMING)
- overall verdict
- fracture map
- strengths
- weaknesses
- narrative issues
- delivery issues
- Q&A vulnerabilities
- suggested next drill / next iteration

Expected outcome:
- a structured review artifact that feels high-value and shareable

Important note:
- this is the hero artifact of the product
- the UI should make this screen feel more important than analytics or forms

### 3.2 Coach
Purpose:
- allow the founder to interact with the post-mortem, ask follow-up questions, and go deeper on how to improve.

Key content / functionality:
- conversational interface
- uses context from the project brief, hackathon brief, pitch, Q&A, and review
- supports follow-up coaching and clarification
- should feel like a post-session critique room, not a generic chatbot

Expected outcome:
- actionable improvement guidance
- better interpretation of the debrief
- continuity into another practice round

