# UX Direction

## Information Architecture
- Primary nav = phases
- Secondary nav = tasks within a phase
- Utility nav = cross-cutting reference views

## Visual Tone
- restrained
- institutional
- intelligent
- soft neutral palette
- structured cards
- minimal ornamentation
- dark mode may be explored later, but current direction is calm, polished, and review-oriented based on the selected reference screens.

## Interaction Principles
- every screen should have one dominant next action
- transitions should reinforce the product journey
- Q&A should only unlock after Pitch is completed
- Debrief should only unlock after Room is completed
- the product should always feel like it is moving the founder toward a stronger next attempt

---

# Non-Goals

This product is not:
- a CRM
- an investor database
- a startup planning suite
- a project management tool
- a general AI note-taking app
- a broad analytics dashboard

It should remain tightly focused on founder rehearsal for demo day.

---

# Build Priorities

Order of implementation:
1. App shell and navigation
2. Brief screens
3. Pitch recording
4. Q&A room
5. Debrief review
6. Coach
7. Sessions
8. Analytics

The product should be built around the shortest convincing end-to-end loop first.

